    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Some ijtikris never grow out of their juvenile stage’s water adaptations, which on Vesk-2 is seen as a fine alternative to being fully adapted to land. Such an ijtikri has the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.universal-creature-rules.tqRguTXDUmQGu8Xp]{Amphibious} trait and the aquatic subtype, as well as a swim speed of 40 feet. The ijtikri also has a better sense of their body in three-dimensional space, and when they are @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.QnGpBSHSTiszjPSb]{Off-Kilter}, they don’t take the normal penalties to attacks and don’t gain the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.MZ8OoH1GE9qDMyCD]{Flat-footed} condition.</p>\n<p><strong>This replaces ijtikri movement.</strong></p>"
    },
